an alpha consumer is someone that plays a key role in connecting with the concept behind a product then adopting that product and finally validating it for the rest of society the term was coined by entertainment economist michael wolf in 1999 and published in his book the entertainment economy the example given by michael wolf in the entertainment economy was the first few people to see the next hot movie the first few people to own a cellular phone the first few people to wear the new pastels and brights all achieve a status boost by being in the know being the one others follow i call these trendsetters alpha consumers theirs is the key role of connecting with the concept behind a product then adopting that product and finally validating it for the rest of society if hits are like explosions alphas are at the epicenter they feel the first vibrations of the explosion and transmit them to the rest of the culture alphas are not the same for every product the women who flocked to the touchy feely movie the bridges of madison county followed their daughters to titanic the college music fans who discovered hootie amp the blowfish were different from the vh1 audience that made them a national phenomenon the first jeep buyers were a far cry from the soccer moms now cruising about in their nine seater suburbans edit references wolf michael the entertainment economy new york random house year 1999 alpha consumer the rice university neologisms database rice university june 10 2008 http neologisms rice edu index php a term amp d 1 amp t 3590 retrieved 2012 11 16 lowry tom february 19 2006 can mtv stay cool business week http www businessweek com magazine content 06 08 b3972001 htm retrieved 2012 11 16 grossman lev august 31 2003 what s next the quest for cool time archived from the original on 2010 06 17 http web archive org web 20100617054735 http www time com time covers 1101030908 xopener html retrieved 2012 11 16 early adopter fans kill studio 60 maybe blog daily intel n